After an upgrade or even after an unclean shutdown of Confluence it is very likely that the plugin cache gets corrupted, which causes _LazyReference$InitializationException: java.lang.NullPointerException_ errors on startup.

This can be fixed by [clearing the plugin cache|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFKB/How+to+Clear+Confluence+Plugins+Cache], however many support tickets could be avoided by having this performed automatically on each startup or at least after an upgrade. The negative impact would be a slightly longer startup.

