When upgrading Confluence, there is sometimes a large delay between when Confluence is started on the new version, and when it actually starts serving pages, due to running upgrade tasks. If the database is very large, and/or there are a lot of schema updates, this can take a very long time to run, and there is no feedback to the user of what is happening other than the log file. In particular, if using the installer, it actually will cause Confluence to open in the web browser, but because it hasn't finished upgrade tasks it will hang for a while and/or time out.

Would it be possible to provide some sort of feedback to indicate what is happening.

For example there could be a placeholder web page running which indicates that Confluence is currently running the upgrade tasks, and show how far through it is.

